narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would highly recommend this course, as I feel like I learned a lot about important issues and themes that have impacted South Asia's history.

If you want an overview of the South Asian political context, take this class! The topics span beyond diversity, equality, and identity towards other themes, so seeing it as an deep dive into the general political context of South Asia is great. The reading amount is fair, and the paper is manageable as long as you start ahead of time. I learned a lot!
Yes. It's not too much work, interesting and engaging.
